thread.title_full: Shaka Smart, Texas land commitment from four-star center James Banks | Dallas Morning News

author: EJ Holland
title: Shaka Smart, Texas land commitment from four-star center James Banks
text:
Shaka Smart is wrecking havoc in Austin.
After landing four-star point guard Jacob Young earlier this offseason, the new Texas head basketball coach reeled in a commitment from four-star La Lumiere (IN) big man James Banks on Thursday.
Banks announced his decision via Twitter.
Hook'Em Horns!! pic.twitter.com/cYBWQAjxH3
— â¬†ï¸Next (@32jbanks) October 8, 2015 Banks committed to Texas over offers from Georgetown, Memphis, Notre Dame, Syracuse, Tennessee, USC and a slew of other major programs.
Banks was rumored to be down to Texas and Vanderbilt. He made his official visit to Texas in late August and followed that up with a trip to Vanderbilt just two weeks later. But in the end, Smart was able to win his second major recruiting battle.
At 6-foot-10, 230 pounds, Banks is ranked as the No. 5 center in the country and No. 2 overall prospect in the state, according to 247Sports Composite.
Texas will likely take three bigs in its 2016 class.
